item.description:
There is the problem: &ldquo;Given an array $a$ of length $n$ where, $1\leq a_i\leq 10^9$ and $1\leq n\leq 10^5$, count the ordered pairs $(i, j)$ such that $i&lt;j$ and $a_i\&amp; a_j = 0$ where $\&amp;$ denotes the bitwise AND operation.&rdquo;
An inexperienced CPer may disregard the constraint on $n$ and write the obvious $\mathcal{O}(n^2)$ solution.
for (int i=0; i&lt;n; ++i){ for (int j=i; j&lt;n; ++j){ ans += (a[i] &amp; a[j]) == 0; } } To test the code I use a randomly generated array with $n=10^5$.
